<h1>About the College of Winterhold</h1>

<div class="about-section">
    <h2>Our History</h2>
    <p>The College of Winterhold was founded in the early First Era by the legendary Archmage Shalidor, who constructed much of the college through powerful magic alone. For over 4,000 years, it has stood as Skyrim's center of magical learning, surviving wars, political upheavals, and even the Great Collapse that claimed most of Winterhold city.</p>

    <p>Despite the skepticism of many Nords, the College has maintained its independence and commitment to magical study, becoming one of the few remaining institutions in Tamriel where all schools of magic are taught without political or religious restriction.</p>
</div>

<div class="about-section">
    <h2>Our Mission & Values</h2>
    <p><strong>To advance magical knowledge</strong> through research, experimentation, and preservation of ancient texts in our Arcanaeum library.</p>

    <p><strong>To train responsible mages</strong> who understand that magic is a tool to be wielded with wisdom, restraint, and ethical consideration.</p>

    <p><strong>To preserve magical heritage</strong> by studying and protecting artifacts, spells, and knowledge that might otherwise be lost to time.</p>

    <p><strong>To serve Skyrim</strong> by providing magical expertise, healing, and protection to those in need, while respecting local laws and customs.</p>
</div>

<div class="about-section">
    <h2>Campus & Facilities</h2>
    <p>The College is built upon the ancient ruins of Saarthal, one of the first Nord cities in Skyrim. Our facilities include:</p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>The Hall of the Elements:</strong> Main courtyard and ritual space for major spellcasting</li>
        <li><strong>The Arcanaeum:</strong> One of Tamriel's largest magical libraries, overseen by Urag gro-Shub</li>
        <li><strong>The Hall of Countenance & Attainment:</strong> Student and faculty living quarters</li>
        <li><strong>The Midden:</strong> Underground chambers for advanced ritual work and artifact storage</li>
        <li><strong>Shalidor's Maze:</strong> A magical testing ground created by the founder himself</li>
    </ul>
</div>

